A vintage 1950s noir-style illustration of a grand hotel lobby at night, viewed from a dramatic low angle. In the foreground, a sleek reception desk with an old-fashioned rotary phone and brass bell. Behind it, a shadowy figure in a bellhop uniform holds a magnifying glass over a guest's wallet, their face half-obscured in darkness. The scene is rendered in muted sepia tones with deep burgundy and gold accents, featuring dramatic venetian blind shadows striping across marble floors. Crystal chandeliers cast suspicious pools of amber light. The atmosphere suggests elegant betrayal and false security, with art deco architectural details framing the scene.
